crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a malicious loader/packer that implements a custom in-memory PE execution engine (Reflective Loader). The program's primary purpose is to decrypt and execute a secondary payload embedded within its own data section. Key malicious behaviors include: 1. Custom Decryption: Function sub_401d70 implements a decryption loop to unpack a data blob located at 0x404040. 2. Manual PE Loading: Functions sub_4015d0, sub_401770, sub_401960, and sub_4019e0 collectively implement a full PE loader. This includes manual allocation of memory (VirtualAlloc), section mapping, base relocation adjustment, and Import Address Table (IAT) resolution using LoadLibraryA/GetProcAddress. 3. Memory Protection Manipulation: Function sub_401850 uses VirtualProtect to set executable permissions on the decrypted sections. 4. Execution: The loader eventually jumps to the entry point of the decrypted in-memory module (eax_1() in sub_401dc0). These techniques are characteristic of sophisticated malware designed to bypass static file scanners and EDR solutions.
